    <bioghist>
      <head>Historical Note</head>
      <p>This collection of vital records was composed by Marion N. Scott between 2018 and 2019 to
        record the deaths, marriages, baptisms, and membership of the Trinitarian Congregational
        Church of Northfield, Massachusetts, between 1878 and 2019. The church, originally founded
        as the Second Congregational Society in 1825, burned down in 1968, and all records at the
        time were lost. These records were produced from questionnaires sent to members as well as
        annual reports following 1968. The Trinitarian Congregational Church continues to serve
        Northfield today.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent>
      <head>Scope and Contents</head>
      <p>This collection records the membership of the Trinitarian Congregational Church of
        Northfield, Massachusetts between 1878 and 2019 through records of marriages, baptisms,
        deaths, and membership.</p>
    </scopecontent>
